{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775848333866,"sessionID":"ses_28733d671ffeWr1nTjwcTuO5y2","part":{"id":"prt_d78cf1c90001ChtMmFp2kjBn64","messageID":"msg_d78ceb86b001RwUth30MjXGx5g","sessionID":"ses_28733d671ffeWr1nTjwcTuO5y2","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:16","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-006 — Sandbox Deletion and Lifecycle Management\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Implement the Sandbox Deletion Handler and Lifecycle Management subsystem in `pkg/workloadmanager` that handles sandbox lifecycle operations including graceful deletion, force deletion, batch deletion, idle timeout detection, and orphan resource cleanup. This component ensures proper resource cleanup, maintains lifecycle state transitions, and provides reliable sandbox termination while integrating with the WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework (AR-004) and the Store (Redis) for session persistence.\n6: \n7: The deletion handler processes `DELETE /v1/sandboxes/:id` and `DELETE /v1/sandboxes` requests, orchestrates graceful shutdown with configurable timeouts, cleans up Kubernetes resources (Sandbox CRs, Pods, Services), and removes session records from the Store.\n8: \n9: ---\n10: \n11: ## Scope\n12: \n13: ### In scope\n14: \n15: | Item | Detail |\n16: |------|--------|\n17: | **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` |\n18: | **HTTP Endpoints** | `DELETE /v1/sandboxes/:id`, `DELETE /v1/sandboxes` (batch), `POST /v1/sandboxes/:id/terminate` (force) |\n19: | **Request types** | `DeleteSandboxRequest` with sandbox ID, `BatchDeleteRequest` with filter criteria |\n20: | **Response types** | `DeleteSandboxResponse` with deletion status, cleaned resources list |\n21: | **Core functionality** | Request validation, graceful shutdown orchestration, resource cleanup, lifecycle state tracking, idle detection, orphan cleanup |\n22: | **Integration with** | dynamic client (Sandbox CRD deletion), Store (session cleanup), HTTP framework (AR-004), Garbage Collector |\n23: | **Error handling** | Not found (404), Conflict (409 - already deleting), Timeout (500), with proper rollback |\n24: \n25: ### Out of scope\n26: \n27: - Sandbox creation logic (handled in AR-005)\n28: - Sandbox update/patch operations (separate AR)\n29: - Authentication/authorization logic (handled by authMiddleware in AR-004)\n30: - HTTP server framework itself (AR-004)\n31: - Store implementation details (external dependency)\n32: - Helm chart modifications\n33: - Multi-cluster deletion coordination\n34: - Sandbox backup/restore before deletion\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## Design\n39: \n40: ### File layout\n41: \n42: | File | Role |\n43: |------|------|\n44: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers.go` | **Modified** — Add `handleDeleteSandbox`, `handleBatchDeleteSandbox`, `handleForceDeleteSandbox` handlers |\n45: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/manager.go` | **NEW** — `LifecycleManager` interface and implementation for orchestrating deletion |\n46: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/shutdown.go` | **NEW** — Graceful shutdown logic with timeout handling |\n47: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/cleanup.go` | **NEW** — Resource cleanup: CR deletion, Pod cleanup, Service cleanup |\n48: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/detector.go` | **NEW** — Idle timeout and orphan detection background workers |\n49: | `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/state.go` | **NEW** — Lifecycle state machine and state transition tracking |\n50: | `pkg/workloadmanager/types/lifecycle.go` | **NEW** — Lifecycle-related type definitions |\n51: | `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` | **Modified** — Add lifecycle constants: `DefaultGracefulTimeout`, `DefaultIdleTimeout` |\n52: \n53: ### Type definitions\n54: \n55: **`DeleteOptions`** — Deletion configuration:\n56: \n57: ```go\n58: // DeleteOptions holds options for sandbox deletion.\n59: type DeleteOptions struct {\n60:     // GracefulTimeout is the timeout for graceful shutdown\n61:     // +kubebuilder:default=\"30s\"\n62:     GracefulTimeout time.Duration `json:\"gracefulTimeout,omitempty\"`\n63: \n64:     // Force deletes immediately without graceful shutdown\n65:     // +kubebuilder:default=false\n66:     Force bool `json:\"force,omitempty\"`\n67: \n68:     // OrphanDependents determines if dependent resources should be orphaned\n69:     // +kubebuilder:default=false\n70:     OrphanDependents bool `json:\"orphanDependents,omitempty\"`\n71: \n72:     // PropagationPolicy for cascading deletion\n73:     PropagationPolicy *metav1.DeletionPropagation `json:\"propagationPolicy,omitempty\"`\n74: }\n75: ```\n76: \n77: **`LifecycleState`** — Sandbox lifecycle states:\n78: \n79: ```go\n80: // LifecycleState represents the lifecycle state of a sandbox.\n81: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Running;Idle;Terminating;Terminated;Failed\n82: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n83: type LifecycleState string\n84: \n85: const (\n86:     // StateRunning indicates the sandbox is active and running\n87:     StateRunning LifecycleState = \"Running\"\n88: \n89:     // StateIdle indicates the sandbox is running but idle\n90:     StateIdle LifecycleState = \"Idle\"\n91: \n92:     // StateTerminating indicates the sandbox is being shut down\n93:     StateTerminating LifecycleState = \"Terminating\"\n94: \n95:     // StateTerminated indicates the sandbox has been deleted\n96:     StateTerminated LifecycleState = \"Terminated\"\n97: \n98:     // StateFailed indicates the sandbox deletion failed\n99:     StateFailed LifecycleState = \"Failed\"\n100: )\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 397. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-006 — Sandbox Deletion and Lifecycle Management\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the Sandbox Deletion Handler and Lifecycle Management subsystem in `pkg/workloadmanager` that handles sandbox lifecycle operations including graceful deletion, force deletion, batch deletion, idle timeout detection, and orphan resource cleanup. This component ensures proper resource cleanup, maintains lifecycle state transitions, and provides reliable sandbox termination while integrating with the WorkloadManager HTTP Service Framework (AR-004) and the Store (Redis) for session persistence.\n\nThe deletion handler processes `DELETE /v1/sandboxes/:id` and `DELETE /v1/sandboxes` requests, orchestrates graceful shutdown with configurable timeouts, cleans up Kubernetes resources (Sandbox CRs, Pods, Services), and removes session records from the Store.\n\n---\n\n## Scope\n\n### In scope\n\n| Item | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **Package** | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` |\n| **HTTP Endpoints** | `DELETE /v1/sandboxes/:id`, `DELETE /v1/sandboxes` (batch), `POST /v1/sandboxes/:id/terminate` (force) |\n| **Request types** | `DeleteSandboxRequest` with sandbox ID, `BatchDeleteRequest` with filter criteria |\n| **Response types** | `DeleteSandboxResponse` with deletion status, cleaned resources list |","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775848333856,"end":1775848333864}}}}
