{"type":"text","timestamp":1775848344305,"sessionID":"ses_28733d671ffeWr1nTjwcTuO5y2","part":{"id":"prt_d78cf2b81001IMgcd1SDkjOd66","messageID":"msg_d78cf2255001vVM6GDZRyOjpA3","sessionID":"ses_28733d671ffeWr1nTjwcTuO5y2","type":"text","text":"The `proposal.md` file for AR-006 has been successfully created at `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md`.\n\n## Summary\n\nThe proposal includes:\n\n### Purpose\nImplement the Sandbox Deletion Handler and Lifecycle Management subsystem in `pkg/workloadmanager` that handles sandbox lifecycle operations including graceful deletion, force deletion, batch deletion, idle timeout detection, and orphan resource cleanup.\n\n### Scope\n- **In scope**: DELETE endpoints (`/v1/sandboxes/:id`, batch delete, force terminate), lifecycle state management, resource cleanup, idle detection, orphan cleanup\n- **Out of scope**: Sandbox creation (AR-005), auth logic (AR-004), Store implementation details, multi-cluster coordination\n\n### Design\n- File layout with 8 new/modified files in `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle/`\n- Type definitions: `DeleteOptions`, `LifecycleState`, `DeleteSandboxResponse`, `IdleDetectionConfig`\n- Deletion flow diagram showing the complete lifecycle\n- Resource cleanup order (CR → Services → Ingress → Store)\n- Lifecycle state machine diagram\n- Idle detection worker implementation\n- Error handling and timeout configuration\n\n### Impact Analysis\n- ~1,060 estimated lines of new code\n- Downstream consumers: HTTP server, Garbage Collector, Store, Sandbox CRD controller\n- Breaking change risk: None (new functionality)\n\n### Alternatives Considered\n1. Synchronous deletion → Rejected (connection timeout issues)\n2. Kubernetes finalizers → Rejected (less control over state tracking)\n3. Single background worker → Rejected (different frequency requirements)\n4. Soft delete with retention → Rejected (complexity, audit handled separately)\n5. Per-resource deletion → Rejected (error-prone, cascading delete preferred)","time":{"start":1775848344302,"end":1775848344302}}}
